results.name: Number of different values of A000005(d) where d is a divisor of n.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
program: (PARI) a(n) = {vals = Set(); fordiv(n, d, vals = Set(concat(vals, numdiv(d)))); return (length(vals));} \\ _Michel Marcus_, Jul 14 2013
xref: Differs from A085082 and A181796 for the first time at n=24, where a(24) = 6, while A085082(24) = A181796(24) = 7.
